  finalObjectiveObject: {fileID: 0}
  finalObjectiveText: {fileID: 0}
  dialogueLines:
  - Welcome Student to the first challenge of Stage One!
  - In this stage, the challenge you will learn is how the AND logic gate works.
  - "The AND (\u2227) gate is a logical operator that checks two conditions."
  - It will only give a TRUE result when both inputs are TRUE.
  - TRUE AND TRUE = TRUE
  - If one or both inputs are FALSE, the result will be FALSE.
  - TRUE AND FALSE = FALSE
  - In this challenge, you must open the gate in front to proceed to the next challenge.
  - Remember, you can only open the gate if BOTH switches are ON.
  - 'If one switch is OFF, the gate will stay closed. '
  - Find a way and investigate the area that might help you open the gate.
  - Good Luck!
  finalDialogueLines: []
  nextSceneName: 
  areAllTasksCompleted: 0
